---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="shuttle ci"
  description="Generate GitHub Actions or GitLab CI pipelines for automated builds and deploys."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    <code>shuttle ci generate</code> produces a ready-to-use CI/CD pipeline configuration for
    GitHub Actions or GitLab CI. The generated file handles Docker image building, pushing to a
    registry, and deploying via SSH using Shuttle.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle ci generate [flags]
</code></pre>

  <h2>Subcommands</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Subcommand</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>generate</code></td>
        <td>Generate a pipeline configuration file for the specified provider</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Flags for <code>ci generate</code></h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--provider &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td><code>github</code></td>
        <td>CI provider: <code>github</code> or <code>gitlab</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--registry &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td><code>ghcr</code></td>
        <td>Docker registry: <code>ghcr</code> or <code>docker-hub</code> (GitHub Actions only)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--branch &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td><code>main</code></td>
        <td>Branch that triggers the deploy pipeline</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--app &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td>from <code>shuttle.yml</code></td>
        <td>Override the app name used in the pipeline. Defaults to the <code>app:</code> value from <code>shuttle.yml</code>.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Output files</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Provider</th>
        <th>Output file</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>GitHub Actions</td>
        <td><code>.github/workflows/shuttle-deploy.yml</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>GitLab CI</td>
        <td><code>.gitlab-ci.yml</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    The directory <code>.github/workflows/</code> is created automatically if it doesn't exist.
  </p>

  <h2>Auto-detection of app name</h2>
  <p>
    When <code>--app</code> is not provided, Shuttle reads the <code>app:</code> field from
    <code>shuttle.yml</code> in the current directory. If no config is found, it defaults to
    <code>my-app</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Examples</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash"># GitHub Actions with GHCR (default)
shuttle ci generate --provider github

# GitHub Actions with Docker Hub
shuttle ci generate --provider github --registry docker-hub

# GitLab CI
shuttle ci generate --provider gitlab

# GitLab CI on a specific branch
shuttle ci generate --provider gitlab --branch production
</code></pre>

  <h2>After generation</h2>
  <p>
    After running the command, configure the required secrets/variables in your CI provider's
    settings. The command prints what is needed:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">Required secrets:
  • DEPLOY_HOST     — Server IP or hostname
  • DEPLOY_USER     — SSH username
  • DEPLOY_SSH_KEY  — SSH private key

GITHUB_TOKEN is provided automatically for GHCR.
</code></pre>
  <p>
    See <a href="/docs/ci/github">GitHub Actions</a> or <a href="/docs/ci/gitlab">GitLab CI</a>
    for full setup instructions.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
